# Google Drive Integration
# To enable Google Drive sync, you need to create a Google Cloud project
# and obtain an OAuth 2.0 Client ID.
#
# Setup instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Create a new project (or select an existing one)
# 3. Enable the Google Drive API:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
#    - Search for "Google Drive API" and enable it
# 4. Configure OAuth consent screen:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "OAuth consent screen"
#    - Select "External" user type
#    - Fill in app name (e.g., "Forgesteel")
#    - Add the scope: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file
# 5. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - Application type: "Web application"
#    - Add Authorized JavaScript origins:
#      - http://localhost:5173 (for development)
#      - https://your-production-domain.com
#    - Copy the Client ID below
#
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
